President Donald J. Trump spoke with Prime Minister Shinzo Abe of Japan to discuss North Korea's recent launch of an intercontinental ballistic missile (ICBM). They both agreed that North Korea poses a direct threat to the United States, Japan, South Korea, and other countries. They committed to increasing economic and diplomatic pressure on North Korea and convincing other countries to do the same. President Trump also reaffirmed the United States' commitment to defend Japan and South Korea from any attack.